=title> Re: Proposed Change in VS Rotation</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> the rotation was set up to stop 1 or 2 guilds contually killing him.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, actually, no, it wasn't.  The rotation was never a charitable device to &quot;spread the wealth&quot; around between guilds.  Instead, it was a gentleman's agreement between the guilds that you are referring to.  The purpose was to reduce conflicts and eliminate the need for those guilds to &quot;race&quot; each other to kill VS.<br>
<br>
That's an important distinction.  The unspoken premise of the rotation system is that VS is a special mob that can only be killed by a small number of guilds.  That is no longer true.  Now some people would like to convert the rotation into a reservation system that guarantees certain guilds a shot at VS.  I just don't see any way that such a system will last for long.  In fact, it may already be dead. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uvisnetalabaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Visnet Alabaster</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#E9D756>(8/12/01 3:43:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Change in VS Rotation</span><hr size=1> Well according to the guild listing Ogmuk has available (which I dont know to be 100% accurate) there are over 100 guilds on EMarr.  There are currently 15 guilds in the rotation.  That seems to be a small number of the total to me. . .Maybe we should all just allow our guild leaders to discuss what they would like to do together. . .<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usagemonprayeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sagemon Prayeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#E9D756>(8/13/01 1:16:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Change in VS Rotation</span><hr size=1> There are a couple problems with that, Visnet.  First of all, when you say that there are over 100 guilds on the server, you're including guilds that have no members over level 30 and guilds that never raid.  Furthermore, there are several additional guilds that are either ready to join the rotation or close to being ready.  The number of guilds in the rotation could reach 20 fairly quickly, and keep growing.  If pickup leaders can join the rotation, the number will get even higher.  Like it or not, you're looking at a scenario under which the rotation would give a guild or pickup leader a shot at VS every 2-3 months.<br>
<br>
Second, I really don't think the guild leaders can do much about the problem.  There are just too many high level players who are either unguilded or in small guilds.  While the top guilds can probably mobilize quickly enough to stop interlopers, many of the guilds in the current rotation do not have that capability.<br>
<br>
There are a lot of people who would love to keep their guaranteed shot at VS.  I just don't see how that sort of arrangement will last for long. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uarsdenyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arsdenyl</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#E9D756>(8/13/01 2:17:38 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.flash.net/~arsmage/ARSSIG.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Change in VS Rotation</span><hr size=1> As mentioned by others many of the tops guilds only want VS for the wizard epic drop. The staves are pure crap, the legs not much better.<br>
<br>
In an effort to get in and complete the wizard epic I expect that things are going to turn FFA shortly. This is good and bad. The good news is that if its a top guild going in and they only need the drop one last time then will leave the rotation, then great. The rotation MIGHT survive that once or twice if everyone elses wait become shorter. The bad is that the drop isn't a guarantee <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
